502–6, 502–11 (2d ed. 1993 and Supp. 2000). This is corroborated
by the State’s choice for many years against revising the applicable
recommended jury instruction (enumerating the complete \\M’Naghten\\
test) in order to match the amended statutory standard. See 1 Gerber,
\\supra,\\ at 502–6 (2d ed. 1993 and Supp. 2000).

  We are satisfied that neither in theory nor in practice did
Arizona’s 1993 abridgment of the insanity formulation deprive Clark of
due process.

# III

  Clark’s second claim of a due process violation challenges the rule
